# Iniciar de Mongo en Linux - Ubuntu 14

## 1. Concepto
	
	Iniciar una instancia de MongoDB
	
## 1. Start MongoDB
	
	p028036@MongoElastic:~$sudo service mongodb start
	p028036@OPME:~$ sudo systemctl start mongodb
	
	p028036@OPME:~$ sudo systemctl status mongodb
		● mongodb.service - An object/document-oriented database
		Loaded: loaded (/lib/systemd/system/mongodb.service; enabled; vendor pres
		Active: active (running) since Thu 2020-02-13 17:32:52 -05; 4s ago
			Docs: man:mongod(1)
		Main PID: 3788 (mongod)
			Tasks: 23 (limit: 4673)
		CGroup: /system.slice/mongodb.service
				└─3788 /usr/bin/mongod --unixSocketPrefix=/run/mongodb --config /
		
		feb 13 17:32:52 OPME systemd[1]: Started An object/document-oriented databas
		lines 1-10/10 (END)

	
## 2. Verify that MongoDB has started successfully

	p028036@MongoElastic:~$vim /var/log/mongodb/mongod.log

## 3. Stop MongoDB

	p028036@MongoElastic:~$sudo service mongodb stop
	p028036@MongoElastic:~$sudo systemctl stop mongodb
	
	p028036@OPME:~$ sudo systemctl status mongodb
		● mongodb.service - An object/document-oriented database
		Loaded: loaded (/lib/systemd/system/mongodb.service; enabled; vendor pres
		Active: inactive (dead) since Thu 2020-02-13 17:30:30 -05; 27s ago
			Docs: man:mongod(1)
		Process: 3118 ExecStart=/usr/bin/mongod --unixSocketPrefix=${SOCKETPATH} -
		Main PID: 3118 (code=exited, status=0/SUCCESS)
		
		feb 13 17:24:34 OPME systemd[1]: Started An object/document-oriented databas
		feb 13 17:30:30 OPME systemd[1]: Stopping An object/document-oriented databa
		feb 13 17:30:30 OPME systemd[1]: Stopped An object/document-oriented databas
		lines 1-10/10 (END)

## 4. Restart MongoDB

	p028036@MongoElastic:~$sudo service mongod restart
	
## 5. Begin using MongoDB

	
	p028036@MongoElastic:~$mongo	


## 6. Estatus de mongo

	p028036@OPME:~$ sudo service mongodb status
	p028036@OPME:~$ sudo systemctl status mongodb
	
	:::
